1
00:00:10,493 --> 00:00:14,066
- What the hell?
- Wait, Nao. It's me.

2
00:00:15,435 --> 00:00:18,640
Suer, I miss you.
Let's go find a dorm together, okay?

3
00:00:18,826 --> 00:00:20,986
- Who are you gonna live with?
- With you, of course.

4
00:00:21,168 --> 00:00:24,835
When are you gonna confess?
You've liked him until we're about to enter college.

5
00:00:25,568 --> 00:00:27,782
What about that person?
What's going on?

6
00:00:28,124 --> 00:00:31,400
I think I'll try opening my heart.
She's pretty cute too.

7
00:00:31,906 --> 00:00:33,622
What about me, Nao?

8
00:00:36,048 --> 00:00:37,831
I like you too.

9
00:00:50,760 --> 00:00:51,950
I'm not sleeping here tonight.

10
00:00:53,370 --> 00:00:54,400
Huh? Why?

11
00:00:54,670 --> 00:00:56,970
- Work.
- You're leaving already?

12
00:00:58,680 --> 00:01:01,360
Yeah. See you. Drive safe.

13
00:01:26,720 --> 00:01:28,790
Tiger still hasn't come home today?

14
00:01:30,860 --> 00:01:32,110
What did you two fight about?

15
00:01:32,330 --> 00:01:35,210
I don't know, Dan.
Things were fine before this.

16
00:01:35,460 --> 00:01:37,860
Since graduation day,
he's changed.

17
00:01:38,120 --> 00:01:40,570
- Since graduation day?
- Yeah.

18
00:01:41,400 --> 00:01:43,460
He said he was going to work with his family.

19
00:01:45,110 --> 00:01:46,930
But I think he's avoiding me.

20
00:01:49,480 --> 00:01:51,630
Tiger probably has his reasons.

21
00:01:52,010 --> 00:01:55,240
Dan thinks when Tiger is okay,
he'll come back by himself.

22
00:01:59,190 --> 00:02:00,580
Don't stress about it.

23
00:02:02,010 --> 00:02:03,520
- You're okay, right?
- Yeah.

24
00:02:03,630 --> 00:02:05,460
Then I will go up to the room first.

25
00:02:17,830 --> 00:02:20,100
Are you busy with work?
Are you coming home today?

26
00:02:40,140 --> 00:02:42,840
Are you okay?
Are you mad at me about something?

27
00:02:43,030 --> 00:02:44,970
Are you coming home today?

28
00:02:45,220 --> 00:02:48,590
Mom made your favorite food today.
Will you come home to eat?

29
00:02:48,900 --> 00:02:50,430
You're okay, right?

30
00:02:50,590 --> 00:02:54,350
If nothing's wrong, can you reply to me?
I'm worried.

31
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:17,040
Suer, you're back?

32
00:03:19,610 --> 00:03:20,810
Why are you sleeping here?

33
00:03:22,100 --> 00:03:26,700
Where did you go?
Why didn't you tell me anything?
Are you mad at me?

34
00:03:27,350 --> 00:03:29,130
Did I do something wrong?

35
00:03:30,550 --> 00:03:33,910
Can you tell me?
No, just tell me, okay?

36
00:03:34,010 --> 00:03:38,350
- If I did something wrong, I'll fix it.
- Hey, what's wrong with you?

37
00:03:39,090 --> 00:03:40,200
Calm down.

38
00:03:40,620 --> 00:03:42,760
You didn't do anything wrong.

39
00:03:43,280 --> 00:03:45,800
- You're avoiding me.
- I'm not.

40
00:03:46,090 --> 00:03:47,990
- I went to work.
- No.

41
00:03:48,160 --> 00:03:49,720
You're really avoiding me.

42
00:03:49,950 --> 00:03:54,470
Don't deny it. Just tell me.
What are you mad at me about?

43
00:03:54,910 --> 00:03:56,310
I'm not mad.

44
00:03:57,360 --> 00:04:00,230
- You're just overthinking it.
- I'm not.

45
00:04:00,770 --> 00:04:06,020
What the hell is wrong with you?
Why won't you tell me? Why keep it to yourself?
Are we not friends anymore?

46
00:04:10,120 --> 00:04:11,370
Nao, calm down first.

47
00:04:13,270 --> 00:04:13,910
Sit down.

48
00:04:15,580 --> 00:04:17,270
Come on, sit down.

49
00:04:22,660 --> 00:04:25,020
What makes you think I'm avoiding you?

50
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:27,990
I know

51
00:04:28,410 --> 00:04:30,150
I might look stupid.

52
00:04:30,470 --> 00:04:34,870
But this time, I really know
that you're trying to avoid me.

53
00:04:34,970 --> 00:04:37,500
You don't come home.
You don't reply to my messages.

54
00:04:37,890 --> 00:04:40,070
You're acting like you're going to disappear from my life.

55
00:04:43,220 --> 00:04:44,370
I was just working.

56
00:04:45,140 --> 00:04:46,320
No.

57
00:04:46,710 --> 00:04:48,420
If you're mad about something, just tell me.

58
00:04:49,110 --> 00:04:52,570
If you don't tell me,
I won't let this end.

59
00:04:55,320 --> 00:04:56,430
I'm not mad at you.

60
00:04:57,750 --> 00:04:58,970
I just...

61
00:04:59,830 --> 00:05:01,100
feel hurt.

62
00:05:02,510 --> 00:05:03,640
Hurt?

63
00:05:04,720 --> 00:05:05,990
Hurt about what?

64
00:05:07,640 --> 00:05:09,390
I feel hurt because

65
00:05:10,190 --> 00:05:11,750
you gave my time to someone else.

66
00:05:13,560 --> 00:05:16,430
- Someone else?
- That person you were talking to.

67
00:05:16,770 --> 00:05:19,320
But I wasn't even talking to them that much.

68
00:05:21,550 --> 00:05:23,150
Then what do you want me to do?

69
00:05:23,350 --> 00:05:28,380
If I talk to them less and spend more time with you,
would that make you okay?

70
00:05:30,590 --> 00:05:31,580
Well?

71
00:05:33,810 --> 00:05:34,590
Yeah.

72
00:05:34,970 --> 00:05:36,870
Then will you stop avoiding me?

73
00:05:37,530 --> 00:05:38,440
I'm not avoiding you.

74
00:05:40,340 --> 00:05:41,850
I really was working.

75
00:05:42,220 --> 00:05:43,950
Yeah, okay.

76
00:05:44,270 --> 00:05:46,310
Are you sure this is the only thing?

77
00:05:47,070 --> 00:05:48,910
What else would I have to feel hurt about?

78
00:05:49,670 --> 00:05:50,750
That's true.

79
00:05:51,310 --> 00:05:56,190
Do you have any more work?
I was thinking we could go to Chiang Mai. Before Dan goes to Boston.

80
00:05:56,490 --> 00:05:57,680
Are you free?

81
00:05:58,530 --> 00:05:59,930
I'll make time for it.

82
00:06:00,510 --> 00:06:01,410
I'll make time for it.So...

83
00:06:02,570 --> 00:06:04,000
We're good now, right?

84
00:06:12,970 --> 00:06:14,370
We're okay now, friend.

85
00:07:59,240 --> 00:08:00,620
Let's go on a trip.

86
00:08:00,780 --> 00:08:03,200
Let's go.

87
00:08:03,360 --> 00:08:07,580
- Suer, do you think the Northern Thai phrases I prepared are okay?
- They're good.

88
00:08:08,220 --> 00:08:09,950
I think they sound pretty natural.

89
00:08:10,440 --> 00:08:12,930
Like you were born in the North.

90
00:08:13,230 --> 00:08:14,410
Yeah, right.

91
00:08:14,880 --> 00:08:17,630
I was born speaking Northern Thai anyway.

92
00:08:17,940 --> 00:08:19,050
It's not true.

93
00:08:19,660 --> 00:08:20,790
Yeah.

94
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:24,430
Nao, are you still talking to that person?

95
00:08:24,680 --> 00:08:25,300
Who?

96
00:08:25,470 --> 00:08:27,710
The one who confessed to you on graduation day.

97
00:08:27,900 --> 00:08:30,380
Oh, we don't talk anymore.

98
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:32,330
Huh? Why did you stop talking?

99
00:08:32,540 --> 00:08:35,860
Probably because of the distance, I guess.
I don't know.

100
00:08:36,410 --> 00:08:39,130
I think it might be the same reason as Mick's.

101
00:08:39,320 --> 00:08:42,160
- It's because you're addicted to games.
- You still haven't stopped teasing me about this?

102
00:08:42,240 --> 00:08:46,650
Isn't it true though? Just let her go.
When I see her, I feel sorry for her.

103
00:08:46,800 --> 00:08:48,780
She can finally find someone new.

104
00:08:49,350 --> 00:08:51,520
Yee and I still love each other.

105
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:54,550
She's just a little mad at me.
We'll make up soon.

106
00:08:56,120 --> 00:09:00,500
Just let her go. I've seen everything Yee has done for you.
You don't see anything.

107
00:09:00,620 --> 00:09:04,240
If I were Yee, I would've left a long time ago.
I wouldn't come back.

108
00:09:04,500 --> 00:09:05,610
Yeah.

109
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:07,490
Really?

110
00:09:07,980 --> 00:09:09,510
She really won't come back?

111
00:09:10,900 --> 00:09:13,380
That's so mean, Mr. Tula.

112
00:09:13,860 --> 00:09:15,580
You're the mean one.

113
00:09:18,980 --> 00:09:20,275
Want to stop at the viewpoint, kids?

114
00:09:20,570 --> 00:09:21,700
Yes.

115
00:09:22,900 --> 00:09:23,930
Are we almost there?

116
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:25,990
Almost.

117
00:09:26,040 --> 00:09:27,110
Hurry up.

118
00:09:27,470 --> 00:09:30,740
- What?
- The trees.

119
00:09:32,810 --> 00:09:34,740
Let's go, let's go.

120
00:09:40,620 --> 00:09:41,940
Dan, let's take a photo here.

121
00:09:42,030 --> 00:09:42,810
Where?

122
00:09:42,870 --> 00:09:43,560
Here?

123
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:45,440
Make a big pose.

124
00:09:45,500 --> 00:09:47,500
One, two, three.

125
00:09:47,580 --> 00:09:50,270
- Got it.
- Dan, let's take a photo.

126
00:09:50,350 --> 00:09:51,410
Come on.

127
00:09:52,370 --> 00:09:54,240
Let's check in.

128
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:01,760
Do I look handsome?

129
00:10:03,180 --> 00:10:04,020
What are you looking at?

130
00:10:05,180 --> 00:10:08,260
Hurry up, come on, take the photo.

131
00:10:09,900 --> 00:10:11,830
- Is it okay?
- Yeah, yeah.

132
00:10:12,150 --> 00:10:12,960
Nao.

133
00:10:15,650 --> 00:10:16,690
Let's take a couple photo.

134
00:10:17,100 --> 00:10:17,890
Mm.

135
00:10:19,730 --> 00:10:21,330
Come on, I'll take it for you.

136
00:10:26,620 --> 00:10:29,710
Ready? One, two, three.

137
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:32,090
One, two, three.

138
00:10:32,390 --> 00:10:34,210
Hey, look at the camera.

139
00:10:35,700 --> 00:10:36,820
I am.

140
00:10:37,080 --> 00:10:39,420
- What are you looking at?
- One, two, three.

141
00:10:39,570 --> 00:10:41,610
Is it okay?

142
00:10:43,510 --> 00:10:44,540
This one is good.

143
00:10:45,120 --> 00:10:46,450
Can we take photos together again sometime?

144
00:10:47,060 --> 00:10:49,090
Sure, no problem.

145
00:11:04,620 --> 00:11:05,420
Let's go.

146
00:11:05,610 --> 00:11:07,200
Have you decided what to wish for?

147
00:11:07,660 --> 00:11:09,880
Not telling.

148
00:12:01,180 --> 00:12:02,060
Handmade keychains.

149
00:12:09,540 --> 00:12:10,620
Why are you holding onto me?

150
00:12:11,140 --> 00:12:13,460
- Nothing.
- Want to buy one for your mom?

151
00:12:15,380 --> 00:12:17,480
I don't think Mom would like it.

152
00:12:23,160 --> 00:12:24,660
- Dan.
- Hmm?

153
00:12:24,860 --> 00:12:26,410
This one is cute.

154
00:12:26,950 --> 00:12:28,100
It suits you.

155
00:12:28,590 --> 00:12:31,260
Really? Doesn't it suit you too?

156
00:12:33,720 --> 00:12:35,400
I think it's too cute.

157
00:12:37,050 --> 00:12:38,060
Then how about this?

158
00:12:38,330 --> 00:12:40,660
I'll buy it for you.
You can take it to Boston.

159
00:12:41,250 --> 00:12:43,180
Then I'll buy one for you too.

160
00:12:43,320 --> 00:12:44,640
So we can use them together.

161
00:12:46,280 --> 00:12:47,170
Together too?

162
00:12:49,420 --> 00:12:50,500
Can I use it too?

163
00:12:50,910 --> 00:12:52,470
How can three of them be a pair?

164
00:12:55,540 --> 00:12:57,260
But Dan's design only has one.

165
00:12:57,720 --> 00:12:59,000
Should we choose another one?

166
00:12:59,490 --> 00:13:01,760
No, Dan likes this one.

167
00:13:02,890 --> 00:13:03,660
Nao.

168
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:07,980
Dan chose this design for you.
Use it with Tiger.

169
00:13:16,860 --> 00:13:18,500
Then you will have to use it alone.

170
00:13:19,420 --> 00:13:21,100
Yeah, it's okay.

171
00:13:21,260 --> 00:13:22,230
I like this design.

172
00:13:22,730 --> 00:13:25,220
What about you? Do you like the one I chose?

173
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:27,300
It's okay.

174
00:13:27,610 --> 00:13:29,110
It doesn't look too cute.

175
00:13:31,520 --> 00:13:32,700
What about you, Suer?

176
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:33,590
What?

177
00:13:35,510 --> 00:13:36,940
I'm okay with it.

178
00:13:39,690 --> 00:13:41,340
Then let's get these three.

179
00:13:54,440 --> 00:13:55,810
Mick, Tul.

180
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:56,880
Hmm?

181
00:13:57,180 --> 00:13:59,790
What's wrong with you two?
You're walking so far apart.

182
00:14:05,480 --> 00:14:07,200
Tul is disgusted by me.

183
00:14:08,690 --> 00:14:09,780
Yeah.

184
00:14:12,210 --> 00:14:13,930
Mr. Tul.

185
00:14:13,980 --> 00:14:15,690
I'm really going to feel hurt now.

186
00:14:17,190 --> 00:14:18,020
I'm just joking.

187
00:14:19,500 --> 00:14:20,410
I don't believe you.

188
00:14:22,300 --> 00:14:23,400
Are you sulking?

189
00:14:26,540 --> 00:14:29,740
There, there. I'll buy you one.
Pick one.

190
00:14:30,040 --> 00:14:31,240
Don't choose an expensive one.

191
00:14:33,270 --> 00:14:34,480
Use it with me.

192
00:14:34,940 --> 00:14:36,020
Why do I have to use it with you?

193
00:14:36,240 --> 00:14:39,200
So it shows that you don't hate me.

194
00:14:39,480 --> 00:14:41,820
And that I'm your best friend.

195
00:14:43,170 --> 00:14:45,000
Fine, pick one.

196
00:14:46,430 --> 00:14:49,060
I should've just tricked you.
Would've saved money.

197
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:51,420
No, this one isn't pretty.

198
00:15:15,290 --> 00:15:16,720
The song sounds nice.

199
00:15:27,180 --> 00:15:28,780
Do you think she is a singer?

200
00:15:30,210 --> 00:15:31,340
She's pretty.

201
00:15:31,520 --> 00:15:32,730
She sings well too.

202
00:15:34,150 --> 00:15:35,210
I don't know.

203
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:48,380
You like this song?

204
00:15:51,180 --> 00:15:52,050
Yeah.

205
00:15:53,110 --> 00:15:54,320
I think it's nice.

206
00:15:55,500 --> 00:15:56,730
I mean, the song is like...

207
00:15:57,360 --> 00:15:59,110
It's not in Northern dialect,

208
00:15:59,960 --> 00:16:02,520
but it has that Northern vibe.

209
00:16:03,070 --> 00:16:04,670
I don't know how to explain it.

210
00:16:22,290 --> 00:16:24,600
So, aren't you going to confess your feelings?

211
00:16:26,020 --> 00:16:28,300
You're about to enter university already.

212
00:16:31,500 --> 00:16:33,000
If I tell him...

213
00:16:33,880 --> 00:16:35,260
What do you think?

214
00:16:39,820 --> 00:16:40,660
I don't know.

215
00:16:43,460 --> 00:16:45,300
But no matter what the answer is,

216
00:16:45,580 --> 00:16:48,090
Duen will never cut you out of his life.

217
00:16:50,150 --> 00:16:50,950
Trust me.

218
00:16:54,280 --> 00:16:56,370
But what if I tell him and he doesn't feel the same?

219
00:17:02,240 --> 00:17:03,620
I think I'd rather stay like this.

220
00:17:51,750 --> 00:17:53,980
Good thing we sent our stuff ahead.

221
00:17:54,110 --> 00:17:56,260
Otherwise, we'd have so much more to carry.

222
00:17:59,320 --> 00:18:00,300
Dan.

223
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:01,660
Yes?

224
00:18:01,900 --> 00:18:03,480
Why do you look sad, honey?

225
00:18:04,260 --> 00:18:06,910
Now that you've come this far, are you feeling sad?

226
00:18:08,030 --> 00:18:09,610
I'm not sad.

227
00:18:09,830 --> 00:18:11,740
I just feel a little overwhelmed.

228
00:18:13,380 --> 00:18:15,700
I've been stuck to Duen for eighteen years.

229
00:18:16,250 --> 00:18:18,240
And stuck to Mom for another eighteen years.

230
00:18:19,540 --> 00:18:22,450
We're just going to be apart. We're not saying goodbye.

231
00:18:22,800 --> 00:18:24,960
Call me when you get there.

232
00:18:25,240 --> 00:18:27,840
If you miss me, you can call anytime.

233
00:18:31,210 --> 00:18:32,170
Come here, give me a hug.

234
00:18:37,660 --> 00:18:39,000
Have a safe trip, Nue.

235
00:18:41,860 --> 00:18:44,820
Take care of Duen for me. Like really good take care.

236
00:18:46,110 --> 00:18:47,690
I should be the one taking care of him.

237
00:18:49,370 --> 00:18:51,920
Let's go. We'll be late.

238
00:18:52,040 --> 00:18:54,040
- Let's go.
- Should we take a picture first?

239
00:18:54,500 --> 00:18:56,280
Oh, sure.

240
00:18:56,570 --> 00:18:58,630
- Then I'll stand in the middle.
- Come on, Mom.

241
00:19:01,810 --> 00:19:03,000
Ready?

242
00:19:03,180 --> 00:19:05,660
1 2 3

243
00:19:07,560 --> 00:19:09,170
Tiger, come take a picture too.

244
00:19:09,300 --> 00:19:10,600
I'll take it for you.

245
00:19:11,180 --> 00:19:12,170
Come on.

246
00:19:12,510 --> 00:19:13,980
Come join us.

247
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:18,470
Look at the camera.

248
00:19:19,470 --> 00:19:22,570
Wow, so handsome.
You're really cute.

249
00:19:22,750 --> 00:19:25,250
1 2 3

250
00:19:32,700 --> 00:19:35,090
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

251
00:19:36,550 --> 00:19:37,200
Come on.

252
00:19:55,910 --> 00:19:57,620
See you at the club this evening.

253
00:19:58,220 --> 00:19:59,420
Okay, see you.

254
00:20:08,550 --> 00:20:10,590
About what I asked you last night, what do you think?

255
00:20:11,220 --> 00:20:12,260
What are you talking about?

256
00:20:14,040 --> 00:20:15,760
The gaming competition.

257
00:20:15,860 --> 00:20:18,370
Me, you, Mick, Ger,

258
00:20:18,510 --> 00:20:19,900
and Get.

259
00:20:21,780 --> 00:20:24,030
Won't Q feel bad about it?

260
00:20:24,660 --> 00:20:26,010
I have something else to do.

261
00:20:27,380 --> 00:20:30,770
Something else? You're just going flirting with girls with Field, aren't you?

262
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:34,520
- You're exaggerating.
- Come on, you're the expert at this.

263
00:20:36,900 --> 00:20:38,520
What about you?

264
00:20:40,460 --> 00:20:43,300
I'm fine with anything. Because I'll be carrying all of you anyway.

265
00:20:43,980 --> 00:20:45,260
Man, my friends...

266
00:20:45,340 --> 00:20:46,860
You're not carrying anyone. I'm the carry.

267
00:20:47,130 --> 00:20:47,730
Seriously.

268
00:20:49,820 --> 00:20:51,140
Hey, let's do this.

269
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:53,280
Ask Mick and Ger first.

270
00:20:53,530 --> 00:20:54,540
See what they think.

271
00:20:54,960 --> 00:20:59,960
Don't forget, if we win,
we'll become the university representatives in the competition.

272
00:21:01,220 --> 00:21:03,770
- Really?
- Yeah, why would I lie to you?

273
00:21:04,190 --> 00:21:08,450
Hey, don't take it too seriously. We already play games together every day.

274
00:21:08,580 --> 00:21:11,730
Besides, it's just practice. Chill.

275
00:21:11,880 --> 00:21:13,910
- Oh.
- Your skills are enough.

276
00:21:15,440 --> 00:21:17,090
- You're such a bragger.
- What?

277
00:21:17,940 --> 00:21:20,020
I'm just stating facts.

278
00:21:20,140 --> 00:21:23,000
Alright, I'll think about it.

279
00:21:23,493 --> 00:21:25,650
- You ask them too.
- Yeah.

280
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:36,160
Why are you late?

281
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:38,700
I went to drop P'Ying off.

282
00:21:39,490 --> 00:21:40,580
You're chasing girls, asshole.

283
00:21:40,750 --> 00:21:44,270
Look who's talking, asshole.
You're obsessed with Nao.

284
00:21:50,630 --> 00:21:52,800
Nao wore my soccer jersey today.

285
00:21:52,960 --> 00:21:54,480
He was so cute.

286
00:21:55,900 --> 00:21:58,590
Your heart's gone. You gave it all away.

287
00:21:58,710 --> 00:21:59,390
Correct.

288
00:22:00,810 --> 00:22:02,940
You like Nao, don't you?

289
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:07,540
- North.
- Ger.

290
00:22:07,930 --> 00:22:08,790
Ger.

291
00:22:09,140 --> 00:22:09,790
Ger.

292
00:22:11,115 --> 00:22:13,210
Damn, you're locking me so tight.

293
00:22:13,720 --> 00:22:14,770
What the hell are you doing?

294
00:22:15,540 --> 00:22:16,820
Asshole.

295
00:22:20,020 --> 00:22:20,610
What?

296
00:22:23,480 --> 00:22:25,090
My dear friend North.

297
00:22:25,320 --> 00:22:27,000
Wow.

298
00:22:27,100 --> 00:22:29,660
My dear friend North, you're not planning to threaten me, are you?

299
00:22:29,977 --> 00:22:30,804
Huh?

300
00:22:32,500 --> 00:22:34,860
- I was just thinking about it.
- Seriously?

301
00:22:35,170 --> 00:22:37,000
I just found out that you like Nao.

302
00:22:37,170 --> 00:22:42,040
- But if you don't want me to tell anyone, I can keep a secret too, you know.
- Oh, come on.

303
00:22:42,480 --> 00:22:45,320
- You? A loudmouth like you keeping a secret?
- Hey!

304
00:22:45,580 --> 00:22:47,650
That's not fair, Tiger.

305
00:22:47,810 --> 00:22:50,300
I’m telling you, when I’m serious,

306
00:22:50,510 --> 00:22:53,690
I can be serious too. Anyway,

307
00:22:53,900 --> 00:22:55,270
Do you really like Nhao?

308
00:22:55,530 --> 00:22:57,000
Damn, this is exciting.

309
00:22:57,170 --> 00:22:59,540
At first, I thought you guys were just close friends.

310
00:22:59,750 --> 00:23:02,340
But this? You secretly like Nao?

311
00:23:04,340 --> 00:23:05,280
Not here, you idiot.

312
00:23:06,600 --> 00:23:07,780
Promise me first.

313
00:23:08,830 --> 00:23:09,850
That you'll keep this a secret.

314
00:23:11,970 --> 00:23:15,970
But seriously, thinking about it, you could just tell Nao.

315
00:23:16,030 --> 00:23:17,320
No way.

316
00:23:17,790 --> 00:23:20,080
If it were that easy, I would've told him ages ago.

317
00:23:21,130 --> 00:23:24,070
- Damn, you're such a coward.
- You don't understand me.

318
00:23:24,700 --> 00:23:26,260
Go practice, then.

319
00:23:26,330 --> 00:23:27,680
You're so hopeless.

320
00:23:27,740 --> 00:23:29,000
Shut up, asshole.

321
00:23:31,940 --> 00:23:35,680
- Keep it down.
- Go practice or get my green tea. Where's my green tea?

322
00:23:35,820 --> 00:23:37,430
- Huh?
- Later.

323
00:23:37,500 --> 00:23:39,400
Buy me one, ok?

324
00:23:45,320 --> 00:23:47,060
Promise me first.

325
00:23:47,550 --> 00:23:50,240
- That you won't tell anyone about this.
- Wow.

326
00:23:50,390 --> 00:23:54,490
- You actually called just to remind me?
- Someone like you can't be trusted.

327
00:23:54,720 --> 00:23:58,590
A deal like this needs something in return, doesn't it?

328
00:23:58,820 --> 00:24:02,000
- What?
- Maybe some snacks.

329
00:24:03,700 --> 00:24:05,590
Fine. Just tell me what you want.

330
00:24:05,850 --> 00:24:07,730
Or green tea works too.

331
00:24:10,540 --> 00:24:13,320
But while I'm gone, take care of Nhao for me, okay?

332
00:24:14,340 --> 00:24:15,530
Don't let anyone bother him.

333
00:24:15,980 --> 00:24:17,490
- Suer.
- With him—

334
00:24:17,640 --> 00:24:18,680
Who are you talking to?

335
00:24:20,900 --> 00:24:21,630
North.

336
00:24:24,630 --> 00:24:25,730
North?

337
00:24:25,810 --> 00:24:27,530
Yeah, it's me. What's up?

338
00:24:28,580 --> 00:24:29,560
North,

339
00:24:29,710 --> 00:24:32,330
I'm streaming games in my room tomorrow. Wanna come?

340
00:24:32,670 --> 00:24:33,450
Sure.

341
00:24:33,980 --> 00:24:35,580
Alright, see you tomorrow then.

342
00:24:35,720 --> 00:24:37,000
Sounds good.

343
00:24:38,140 --> 00:24:39,000
I'm going to the bathroom first.

344
00:25:00,830 --> 00:25:02,640
Nao, I'm here.

345
00:25:02,740 --> 00:25:04,810
- Suer, can you open the door for him?
- Dude.

346
00:25:07,000 --> 00:25:08,280
Coming.

347
00:25:12,040 --> 00:25:13,990
Hey dude, come to say hi.

348
00:25:15,190 --> 00:25:17,820
Hello. I'm North.

349
00:25:17,970 --> 00:25:19,420
The man from Engineering.

350
00:25:20,340 --> 00:25:21,330
Yay.

351
00:25:21,520 --> 00:25:23,470
Sounds good?

352
00:25:23,590 --> 00:25:24,620
North.

353
00:25:24,820 --> 00:25:27,150
Can you read the comments for me? I'm playing the game.

354
00:25:27,250 --> 00:25:28,230
I can't really read them properly.

355
00:25:28,900 --> 00:25:29,870
Sure.

356
00:25:31,960 --> 00:25:32,840
Hey.

357
00:25:33,130 --> 00:25:34,070
Here it is.

358
00:25:35,260 --> 00:25:37,660
They want you to review the new skin, bro.

359
00:25:38,320 --> 00:25:40,070
The new skin?

360
00:25:41,110 --> 00:25:43,730
Well, about the new skin, I think...

361
00:25:44,600 --> 00:25:48,950
It's pretty okay, but personally I don't really like it that much.
I'll give it around 7 out of 10.

362
00:25:49,100 --> 00:25:51,220
You even rate it?

363
00:25:51,540 --> 00:25:57,000
Hey, this one says, "I miss you so much, P'Tiger."

364
00:25:58,940 --> 00:26:01,640
Hey, someone misses you, Tiger.

365
00:26:02,660 --> 00:26:03,910
You stream with him too?

366
00:26:05,270 --> 00:26:09,930
Yeah, Tiger used to stream a lot at first, but he doesn't anymore.

367
00:26:10,630 --> 00:26:12,630
Tiger, come here for a sec.

368
00:26:14,350 --> 00:26:15,810
Nah, I'm too lazy.

369
00:26:15,900 --> 00:26:19,420
Come on, you're not helping at all.

370
00:26:19,940 --> 00:26:22,460
Look, they're asking about you a lot.

371
00:26:22,570 --> 00:26:23,970
No.

372
00:26:24,150 --> 00:26:25,480
Such a cold man, huh?

373
00:26:28,870 --> 00:26:29,940
Read this one for me.

374
00:26:30,590 --> 00:26:33,750
"Does Tiger have a girlfriend yet?"

375
00:26:33,900 --> 00:26:37,090
Suer? No, he doesn't have one right now.

376
00:26:37,370 --> 00:26:39,180
You can try hitting on him.

377
00:26:39,590 --> 00:26:42,260
I actually want him to have a girlfriend too.

378
00:26:42,380 --> 00:26:43,580
"Damn you."

379
00:26:47,320 --> 00:26:52,170
Streaming early today? I just got out of class. Did you bring a friend with you? Your friend is cute too.

380
00:26:52,340 --> 00:26:55,100
Thanks, P'Tar, for the 1000 bits.

381
00:26:57,900 --> 00:26:59,840
Thank you for the 1000 bits.

382
00:27:02,570 --> 00:27:04,540
Thank you too, P'Gun.

383
00:27:05,270 --> 00:27:06,650
You can actually read it?

384
00:27:07,740 --> 00:27:09,180
How did you know his name is Gun?

385
00:27:09,640 --> 00:27:13,380
Oh, this account has been following me since the beginning.

386
00:27:13,490 --> 00:27:15,910
So I asked his name. He said his name was Gun.

387
00:27:16,780 --> 00:27:19,670
I call him P'Gun because I thought he was probably older than me.

388
00:27:22,160 --> 00:27:25,940
I was so tired from class today.
Having Nong Nao here really healed me.

389
00:27:26,000 --> 00:27:27,920
I feel better now. Thank you.

390
00:27:29,900 --> 00:27:31,790
What the hell is wrong with you?

391
00:27:34,180 --> 00:27:37,500
You again? Why do you always pick a fight with me?

392
00:27:38,720 --> 00:27:39,650
Hey.

393
00:27:45,950 --> 00:27:46,640
Hey.

394
00:27:47,050 --> 00:27:48,240
They're fighting now, bro.

395
00:27:50,610 --> 00:27:55,660
Thank you both for sending those in. I appreciate it,
but let's all get along, okay?

396
00:27:56,480 --> 00:27:59,330
See? Nong Nao said not to fight.

397
00:27:59,570 --> 00:28:00,940
Then get the hell out of here.

398
00:28:03,150 --> 00:28:05,950
Uh, I think I'll stop the stream here for today.

399
00:28:06,150 --> 00:28:09,280
I'll come back again later. Thank you, everyone.

400
00:28:09,410 --> 00:28:10,440
Turn it off. Turn it off.

401
00:28:11,340 --> 00:28:12,590
Damn.

402
00:28:13,900 --> 00:28:15,490
You're something else, you know.

403
00:28:16,280 --> 00:28:18,890
Gotcha.

404
00:28:26,260 --> 00:28:29,700
Hey Suer, North asked us to join a gaming competition.
Are you interested?

405
00:28:31,040 --> 00:28:32,250
A gaming competition?

406
00:28:32,590 --> 00:28:35,420
Yeah, he asked me to invite you and Mick too.

407
00:28:37,120 --> 00:28:38,300
Are you joining?

408
00:28:38,690 --> 00:28:41,330
I think it's interesting. Sounds fun.

409
00:28:43,890 --> 00:28:44,780
Sure, let's do it.

410
00:28:46,213 --> 00:28:47,475
I'll go with whatever you want.

411
00:28:48,820 --> 00:28:50,770
Alright, we're joining then.

412
00:28:51,210 --> 00:28:51,940
Yeah.

413
00:28:52,480 --> 00:28:54,530
Oh, and what about Mick?

414
00:28:55,190 --> 00:28:56,770
I'll ask him.

415
00:28:57,100 --> 00:28:59,460
Alright, I'll leave it to you then.

416
00:29:10,630 --> 00:29:12,120
Students,

417
00:29:12,180 --> 00:29:15,620
please pair up for this assignment.

418
00:29:20,690 --> 00:29:21,730
Hey.

419
00:29:21,990 --> 00:29:24,182
- Do you have a partner yet?
- Oh, yeah, I do.

420
00:29:29,690 --> 00:29:32,040
Um, do you have a partner?

421
00:29:32,830 --> 00:29:35,820
- I don't have one yet.
- Me neither.

422
00:29:36,100 --> 00:29:38,840
If you don't mind, would you like to work with me?

423
00:29:38,940 --> 00:29:39,580
Sure.

424
00:29:39,920 --> 00:29:41,780
I'm Duennao.

425
00:29:42,070 --> 00:29:43,690
I'm Lin, from the Faculty of Education.

426
00:29:43,800 --> 00:29:46,520
Are you in Engineering, Duennao?

427
00:29:48,150 --> 00:29:49,850
You can just call me Nao.

428
00:29:50,710 --> 00:29:51,280
And yes.

429
00:29:51,370 --> 00:29:53,000
I'm in Electrical Engineering.

430
00:29:53,060 --> 00:29:53,880
Oh.

431
00:29:54,060 --> 00:29:56,500
Did you come to class alone today?

432
00:29:56,700 --> 00:29:58,860
Yeah, I did.

433
00:29:59,060 --> 00:30:02,320
- My friends all went to other classes.
- Same here.

434
00:30:02,830 --> 00:30:03,700
Hey...

435
00:30:04,810 --> 00:30:06,520
Can I have your Line?

436
00:30:06,690 --> 00:30:08,560
- So we can discuss the assignment.
- Sure.

437
00:30:12,500 --> 00:30:13,520
Thanks.

438
00:30:16,500 --> 00:30:17,580
What are we supposed to do?

439
00:30:17,650 --> 00:30:20,540
She wants us to pair up. Then we'll have to present.

440
00:30:23,540 --> 00:30:25,940
- How are you getting home, Lin?
- I'll call a ride here.

441
00:30:26,180 --> 00:30:27,280
Oh.

442
00:30:28,790 --> 00:30:31,300
I'll text you. Bye, get home safely.

443
00:30:31,400 --> 00:30:33,920
- Bye, get home safely too.
- Bye.

444
00:30:36,920 --> 00:30:37,780
Who was that?

445
00:30:39,280 --> 00:30:40,080
Just now?

446
00:30:40,560 --> 00:30:42,560
Lin. My new friend from class.

447
00:30:43,180 --> 00:30:44,930
If it wasn't for my major classes,

448
00:30:45,220 --> 00:30:46,130
I'd be studying with you.

449
00:30:46,560 --> 00:30:48,660
You should spend some time apart from me.

450
00:30:50,010 --> 00:30:51,730
So you don't have to study alone.

451
00:30:52,780 --> 00:30:54,120
Damn, North...

452
00:30:54,220 --> 00:30:57,680
- He knows nothing.
- I can study alone, you know.

453
00:30:57,820 --> 00:30:59,280
It's fine. Chill.

454
00:30:59,470 --> 00:31:01,220
I just made a new friend.

455
00:31:02,290 --> 00:31:03,810
Come on, I'm hungry.

456
00:31:04,910 --> 00:31:05,960
Let's eat.

457
00:31:07,540 --> 00:31:08,770
Let's go.

458
00:31:14,500 --> 00:31:17,000
Yeah. Do you have any work today, Lin?

459
00:31:20,270 --> 00:31:21,710
I’ve got a ton of work.

460
00:31:23,530 --> 00:31:24,930
That’s a lot.

461
00:31:25,220 --> 00:31:27,680
- And I don’t understand anything in class.
- Nao, let’s practice gaming.

462
00:31:27,950 --> 00:31:29,000
Mm.

463
00:31:30,210 --> 00:31:33,620
- Yeah.
- Nao.

464
00:31:34,510 --> 00:31:36,850
- Hey, you talking to me?
- Yeah.

465
00:31:37,190 --> 00:31:38,550
Wanna practice gaming today?

466
00:31:39,830 --> 00:31:41,400
I’ve got work today.

467
00:31:42,290 --> 00:31:43,260
Maybe next time.

468
00:31:44,510 --> 00:31:47,590
Uh-huh. Hello, Lin? Yeah.

469
00:31:47,940 --> 00:31:49,000
My friend just came by.

470
00:31:50,870 --> 00:31:52,860
Yeah, it’s a gaming competition at our university.

471
00:31:53,300 --> 00:31:55,000
If you’re free, come watch.

472
00:32:03,400 --> 00:32:04,320
Nao.

473
00:32:04,940 --> 00:32:05,690
Hm?

474
00:32:06,540 --> 00:32:07,540
That girl…

475
00:32:08,110 --> 00:32:09,090
Are you still talking to her?

476
00:32:09,830 --> 00:32:11,000
Mm.

477
00:32:11,540 --> 00:32:12,810
Why are you talking to her?

478
00:32:14,110 --> 00:32:15,990
She’s kind of cute, you know.

479
00:32:17,790 --> 00:32:19,060
I’m sleepy.

480
00:32:19,750 --> 00:32:20,880
I’m going to sleep.

481
00:32:21,140 --> 00:32:22,340
So tired.

482
00:32:49,780 --> 00:32:51,840
- Where are you going?
- I’ve got a date with Lin.

483
00:32:53,250 --> 00:32:54,470
Can’t you skip it?

484
00:32:57,250 --> 00:32:58,220
I think…

485
00:32:58,730 --> 00:32:59,960
there’s something off about Lin.

486
00:33:01,310 --> 00:33:02,410
What do you mean?

487
00:33:03,910 --> 00:33:05,130
I don’t know.

488
00:33:06,610 --> 00:33:09,300
I just don’t want you getting involved with her.

489
00:33:10,030 --> 00:33:11,380
Can you stop talking to her?

490
00:33:14,580 --> 00:33:15,650
I don’t like it.

491
00:33:17,930 --> 00:33:19,420
Don’t be ridiculous, Suer.

492
00:33:19,800 --> 00:33:21,540
You’re overthinking it.

493
00:33:21,930 --> 00:33:23,040
I’m going now.

494
00:33:32,380 --> 00:33:35,000
Yes! It’s over!

495
00:33:35,020 --> 00:33:38,290
Push! I bet already—end it!

496
00:33:38,340 --> 00:33:40,910
Hit the tower! Focus the tower!

497
00:33:40,940 --> 00:33:43,830
Nice, go in—focus the tower!

498
00:33:43,960 --> 00:33:44,900
Hurry!

499
00:33:44,960 --> 00:33:47,140
Yeah!

500
00:33:47,300 --> 00:33:49,280
Free star.

501
00:33:49,490 --> 00:33:52,370
Sorry, I’m late. I just dropped Lin off.

502
00:33:54,190 --> 00:33:55,460
You’re serious about this?

503
00:33:55,750 --> 00:33:58,920
- About what?
- About Lin. Are you really serious about her?

504
00:33:59,080 --> 00:34:00,700
Yeah, I’m talking to Lin.

505
00:34:01,200 --> 00:34:02,750
She’s kinda cute though.

506
00:34:04,940 --> 00:34:08,060
- You, seriously?
- Yeah, why?

507
00:34:08,380 --> 00:34:10,000
Nonsense. I don’t think you actually like her.

508
00:34:10,120 --> 00:34:13,420
How would you know who I like or don’t like, huh, North?

509
00:34:13,490 --> 00:34:14,690
I feel bad for my friend.

510
00:34:14,780 --> 00:34:16,000
Come on, let’s practice.

511
00:34:16,240 --> 00:34:18,340
What about Tiger? Didn’t he come with you?

512
00:34:18,520 --> 00:34:20,140
He didn’t. He said he had work.

513
00:34:20,340 --> 00:34:22,380
Here, let Field fill in for him.

514
00:34:23,300 --> 00:34:24,170
Let’s go.

515
00:34:24,840 --> 00:34:26,300
Come on.

516
00:34:39,850 --> 00:34:40,650
What?

517
00:34:41,290 --> 00:34:43,240
Where are you? Dad wants to see you.

518
00:34:43,380 --> 00:34:44,290
Says it’s important.

519
00:34:51,800 --> 00:34:54,440
Did something happen? You called me here so suddenly.

520
00:34:59,530 --> 00:35:01,670
You have to get married.

521
00:35:02,000 --> 00:35:03,750
To expand our influence

522
00:35:03,870 --> 00:35:06,650
and make it even bigger and wider.

523
00:35:08,250 --> 00:35:10,270
I’ve already talked to the other side.

524
00:35:10,860 --> 00:35:12,340
It’s just this one matter.

525
00:35:12,900 --> 00:35:14,280
You can do it, right?

526
00:35:19,250 --> 00:35:19,840
Yes.

527
00:35:29,070 --> 00:35:30,180
Are you okay?

528
00:35:31,300 --> 00:35:32,160
About the marriage.

529
00:35:36,110 --> 00:35:37,630
I don’t care.

530
00:35:39,980 --> 00:35:41,060
And P’Ben?

531
00:35:43,080 --> 00:35:43,950
What about Ben?

532
00:35:44,780 --> 00:35:46,850
I thought you two were dating.

533
00:35:47,350 --> 00:35:49,330
No, we’re not dating.

534
00:35:50,300 --> 00:35:51,350
Just friends.

535
00:35:52,580 --> 00:35:54,420
So you only see him as a friend?

536
00:35:55,970 --> 00:35:57,290
Or does he see you as just a friend?

537
00:35:59,420 --> 00:36:00,900
Both of us.

538
00:36:10,111 --> 00:36:12,800
Are you free tomorrow? Let’s go get dessert.

539
00:36:17,000 --> 00:36:17,990
Why...

540
00:36:18,400 --> 00:36:20,010
are you suddenly asking me?

541
00:36:20,370 --> 00:36:22,460
We haven’t hung out like this in a while.

542
00:36:23,070 --> 00:36:25,060
I know you’re a bit upset with me

543
00:36:25,230 --> 00:36:26,550
for not having time for you.

544
00:36:27,060 --> 00:36:29,210
Hey, why are you ordering so little?

545
00:36:29,420 --> 00:36:31,560
- Order more. I’ll treat you.
- Really?

546
00:36:31,780 --> 00:36:32,470
Yeah.

547
00:36:33,300 --> 00:36:35,000
Wait for me a sec.

548
00:36:35,730 --> 00:36:36,680
A sec?

549
00:36:37,730 --> 00:36:38,630
Why?

550
00:36:40,270 --> 00:36:41,550
Lin.

551
00:36:42,620 --> 00:36:44,640
Sorry I’m late.

552
00:36:44,710 --> 00:36:46,820
It’s okay. Do you want anything?

553
00:36:47,377 --> 00:36:48,840
Order whatever, I’ll treat you.

554
00:36:52,020 --> 00:36:54,450
You’re Nao’s friend, right? I’m Lin.

555
00:37:03,260 --> 00:37:04,500
Suer.

556
00:37:14,140 --> 00:37:17,550
Sorry about today, Lin. My friend’s acting weird, I don’t know why.

557
00:37:19,540 --> 00:37:23,470
It’s okay. Thanks for the dessert.

558
00:37:28,690 --> 00:37:29,970
Where were you, Suer?

559
00:37:30,760 --> 00:37:32,300
Can we talk?

560
00:37:32,540 --> 00:37:33,770
I’ve got nothing to talk about.

561
00:37:34,740 --> 00:37:36,650
How long is this going to go on?

562
00:37:37,630 --> 00:37:39,820
I know you don’t like it

563
00:37:40,090 --> 00:37:41,770
when I get close to other people.

564
00:37:42,490 --> 00:37:44,050
But what you did today…

565
00:37:44,440 --> 00:37:45,940
wasn’t too much?

566
00:37:46,930 --> 00:37:48,000
And what about you?

567
00:37:48,540 --> 00:37:49,395
Is that so great?

568
00:37:49,506 --> 00:37:51,946
- What did I do?
- You set me up with her.

569
00:37:53,770 --> 00:37:55,370
We’re best friends.

570
00:37:55,730 --> 00:37:58,480
I just wanted the person I like to be close to you too.

571
00:37:58,650 --> 00:38:00,960
- That’s all.
- Did you ever ask me?

572
00:38:01,100 --> 00:38:02,610
If I even wanted that?

573
00:38:03,270 --> 00:38:05,150
Why do you hate Lin so much?

574
00:38:05,320 --> 00:38:06,830
If you keep closing yourself off like this…

575
00:38:07,090 --> 00:38:10,670
- how would you know what she’s like?
- I don’t want to know.

576
00:38:13,800 --> 00:38:15,320
What’s wrong with you, Suer?

577
00:38:15,710 --> 00:38:19,650
Every time I get close to someone, why are you always like this?

578
00:38:21,000 --> 00:38:23,460
- I don’t like it.
- Then what do you want me to do?

579
00:38:23,650 --> 00:38:26,150
- You don’t want me to have anyone?
- Yeah.

580
00:38:28,260 --> 00:38:30,000
You’re so selfish.

581
00:38:30,570 --> 00:38:33,000
Who I like is my business.

582
00:38:36,370 --> 00:38:37,470
Fine.

583
00:38:38,830 --> 00:38:40,440
I’m just your friend, right?

584
00:38:40,940 --> 00:38:42,550
Sorry for being selfish.

585
00:38:44,770 --> 00:38:47,920
Suer… Suer.

586
00:39:14,930 --> 00:39:17,420
Will you finally tell me what’s wrong?

587
00:40:03,330 --> 00:40:04,740
Have you contacted Ben?

588
00:40:05,057 --> 00:40:07,890
- Mr. Ben has resigned.
- What?!

589
00:40:08,180 --> 00:40:10,080
The boss is considering it.

590
00:40:10,460 --> 00:40:13,110
But Mr. Ben insists on resigning.

591
00:40:19,140 --> 00:40:20,460
What does Dad say?

592
00:40:20,880 --> 00:40:23,520
The boss told him to do something.

593
00:40:23,880 --> 00:40:26,390
If he succeeds, he’ll be allowed to resign.

594
00:40:28,660 --> 00:40:31,000
Go find out what Dad made him do.

595
00:40:31,635 --> 00:40:32,422
Yes, sir.

596
00:40:49,000 --> 00:40:50,820
You’re really going through with this, Nao?

597
00:40:51,420 --> 00:40:53,390
Why does everyone have to worry

598
00:40:53,940 --> 00:40:55,690
just because I like someone?

599
00:40:57,190 --> 00:40:59,300
I just feel bad for Lin.

600
00:40:59,950 --> 00:41:01,880
You don’t really like her that much.

601
00:41:04,680 --> 00:41:08,130
Look, even now you still haven't replied to their chat

602
00:41:08,260 --> 00:41:09,060
You see?

603
00:41:09,850 --> 00:41:12,900
How am I supposed to reply? I'm talking with you.

604
00:41:13,150 --> 00:41:17,400
- If I reply, I’d be being rude to you
- Oh please, manners

605
00:41:17,500 --> 00:41:19,930
Look at you, talking about manners.

606
00:41:20,790 --> 00:41:22,340
Fine, whatever.

607
00:41:24,857 --> 00:41:26,380
So how is Suer doing?

608
00:41:26,530 --> 00:41:27,880
He didn’t come back to the room yesterday

609
00:41:28,180 --> 00:41:31,610
- Was he with you?
- You care more about Suer than Lin

610
00:41:31,980 --> 00:41:34,400
Why would I be worried about Lin?

611
00:41:34,750 --> 00:41:38,390
Lin’s fine. Suer’s the one who seems more worrying

612
00:41:38,580 --> 00:41:40,190
You don’t even need to care about him

613
00:41:40,400 --> 00:41:42,110
You’ve got more important people to care about

614
00:41:42,500 --> 00:41:44,400
Reply now, or she will get mad.

615
00:41:49,670 --> 00:41:51,800
Yeah, I replied

616
00:41:52,370 --> 00:41:53,990
So how is Suer doing?

617
00:41:55,970 --> 00:41:57,430
Hey, Nao

618
00:41:57,560 --> 00:42:00,180
- I really don’t want you dating her
- Why?

619
00:42:00,400 --> 00:42:02,130
Why is it that every time I try to love someone

620
00:42:02,370 --> 00:42:06,410
there are always obstacles—and you guys are the obstacle

621
00:42:07,480 --> 00:42:09,210
You’re so dumb, as always

622
00:42:09,500 --> 00:42:11,860
You still don’t even realize you don’t like her

623
00:42:12,180 --> 00:42:14,650
And I’m telling you this because I feel sorry for Lin

624
00:42:14,820 --> 00:42:17,700
You’re just excited because someone new came in

625
00:42:18,180 --> 00:42:20,420
And she’s cute
I know

626
00:42:20,660 --> 00:42:23,540
what kind of person you are—you’ll talk to anyone.

627
00:42:26,540 --> 00:42:28,680
Hey, you have a brother, right?

628
00:42:28,940 --> 00:42:30,670
Why don’t you try talking to your brother?

629
00:42:30,840 --> 00:42:33,870
I think your brother is probably the one who understands you best.

630
00:42:34,300 --> 00:42:35,360
Try talking to him.

631
00:42:35,620 --> 00:42:37,000
Maybe you’ll get something good out of it.

632
00:42:38,250 --> 00:42:39,450
Call him now.

633
00:42:46,070 --> 00:42:48,620
- What time is it in Boston right now?
- How would I know?

634
00:42:49,350 --> 00:42:50,310
It’s 5 AM

635
00:42:50,460 --> 00:42:52,090
Dan should be awake now.

636
00:42:52,220 --> 00:42:55,580
If he’s awake, just call him. I’m here too, I’ll tell him.

637
00:42:57,180 --> 00:42:57,960
I’m calling him.

638
00:43:04,220 --> 00:43:05,600
What do you think?

639
00:43:06,120 --> 00:43:10,720
If I'm wrong, just tell me—so he can punish me with two kicks.

640
00:43:12,290 --> 00:43:14,168
- Kick your face?
- Your face.

641
00:43:16,100 --> 00:43:18,840
- You really fought Tiger over this?
- Yeah.

642
00:43:19,230 --> 00:43:20,740
Pretty much, Dan.

643
00:43:21,510 --> 00:43:23,270
I don’t know what to do anymore.

644
00:43:23,570 --> 00:43:25,420
Looks like you might actually like this girl.

645
00:43:25,650 --> 00:43:27,660
Since you even fought Tiger over it.

646
00:43:27,900 --> 00:43:31,000
But like North said, maybe it’s just excitement.

647
00:43:31,310 --> 00:43:34,290
You never had anyone this nice

648
00:43:34,580 --> 00:43:36,360
and you like this much before.

649
00:43:36,620 --> 00:43:39,520
I'm sure how much you like her.

650
00:43:39,720 --> 00:43:41,900
Maybe it’s love, maybe just excitement.

651
00:43:42,240 --> 00:43:43,990
We’ll just have to wait and see a bit more.

652
00:43:44,660 --> 00:43:46,880
But in the meantime, you’ll keep fighting with Tiger.

653
00:43:47,090 --> 00:43:49,000
Don’t you think Suer should try to understand me a bit?

654
00:43:49,570 --> 00:43:51,820
He can’t keep sulking like this all the time, right?

655
00:43:52,310 --> 00:43:54,220
At this rate I’ll stay single forever.

656
00:43:56,240 --> 00:43:57,370
I don’t know.

657
00:43:57,820 --> 00:44:00,600
- North, what do you think?
- I don’t know either.

658
00:44:01,110 --> 00:44:04,500
But if he’s too controlling, just dump him then.

659
00:44:05,080 --> 00:44:06,390
If he won’t give in

660
00:44:06,510 --> 00:44:07,820
and you won’t give in.

661
00:44:08,250 --> 00:44:09,810
Just break up the friendship, what?

662
00:44:10,050 --> 00:44:13,770
- That’s my best friend, my ride-or-die
- But he won’t let you have a girlfriend.

663
00:44:14,370 --> 00:44:17,260
You’ve got to choose a side then, right, Dannue?

664
00:44:17,340 --> 00:44:18,860
North is right.

665
00:44:19,380 --> 00:44:21,160
Since Tiger won’t give in

666
00:44:21,480 --> 00:44:22,750
and you won’t give in.

667
00:44:23,410 --> 00:44:26,060
- There’s no other choice
- I don’t want that.

668
00:44:27,070 --> 00:44:30,250
I’ll talk to him again. Thanks, Dan.

669
00:44:30,670 --> 00:44:34,420
- We’ll call again later
- Sure, see you, Duen.

670
00:44:41,640 --> 00:44:42,580
North.

671
00:44:42,820 --> 00:44:44,620
Have you ever felt like this with a friend?

672
00:44:45,540 --> 00:44:47,510
No. With friends

673
00:44:47,780 --> 00:44:48,850
I’m not that intense.

674
00:44:50,460 --> 00:44:51,730
I get you though.

675
00:44:52,880 --> 00:44:55,220
You’ve never had a ride-or-die friend like me.

676
00:44:57,110 --> 00:44:59,870
I feel bad even calling you a cow.

677
00:45:01,790 --> 00:45:02,900
What cow are you talking about.

678
00:45:17,800 --> 00:45:19,280
You went to see your dad?

679
00:45:22,060 --> 00:45:23,000
How was it?

680
00:45:25,000 --> 00:45:26,290
Same as always

681
00:45:31,840 --> 00:45:32,720
Not drinking?

682
00:45:33,810 --> 00:45:35,460
Just a little.

683
00:45:48,070 --> 00:45:50,330
No problem leaving work like this?

684
00:45:53,720 --> 00:45:55,530
This is probably the best way.

685
00:45:58,200 --> 00:45:59,260
And you?

686
00:46:00,240 --> 00:46:01,740
About P’Ben.

687
00:46:05,800 --> 00:46:07,420
He’s trying to shut me out.

688
00:46:09,150 --> 00:46:10,340
So what now?

689
00:46:13,640 --> 00:46:15,410
I’m not letting him resign.

690
00:46:17,000 --> 00:46:19,340
We’ve worked together for over ten years.

691
00:46:20,020 --> 00:46:22,130
How can I just let him leave like that.

692
00:46:22,510 --> 00:46:23,890
Is that really the reason?

693
00:46:47,130 --> 00:46:49,890
You guys know where Suer is, right?

694
00:46:53,000 --> 00:46:54,390
We really don’t know.

695
00:46:57,000 --> 00:46:58,690
Did he tell you not to tell me?

696
00:47:00,260 --> 00:47:01,540
Why?

697
00:47:02,930 --> 00:47:04,700
We really don’t know, Nao.

698
00:47:05,260 --> 00:47:07,280
He hasn’t contacted us either.

699
00:47:09,040 --> 00:47:10,440
Yeah, I think

700
00:47:10,940 --> 00:47:14,700
he’s probably just off doing his own thing, like always.

701
00:47:16,170 --> 00:47:18,630
So, you guys really don’t know, right?

702
00:47:24,760 --> 00:47:25,870
How’s Nao doing, huh?

703
00:47:26,740 --> 00:47:28,320
If you want to know, go see for yourself.

704
00:47:28,680 --> 00:47:30,380
He’s been asking about you.

705
00:47:30,700 --> 00:47:33,930
But we couldn’t tell him anything, because we don’t know where you are either.

706
00:47:35,420 --> 00:47:36,290
That’s good.

707
00:47:36,870 --> 00:47:40,080
So, how much longer are you going to keep this up?

708
00:47:41,570 --> 00:47:42,940
I don’t know.

709
00:47:44,320 --> 00:47:45,900
But if

710
00:47:47,050 --> 00:47:48,950
I have to see him with someone else

711
00:47:51,220 --> 00:47:52,440
I can’t handle it.

712
00:47:53,220 --> 00:47:56,090
Alright, if you need anything, just tell me.

713
00:47:56,950 --> 00:47:58,390
Please take care of Nao for me.

714
00:48:18,280 --> 00:48:19,260
Thank you.

715
00:48:28,150 --> 00:48:30,540
This one is really good. Nao, try it.

716
00:48:35,400 --> 00:48:36,470
Nao.

717
00:48:38,580 --> 00:48:39,440
Nao.

718
00:48:41,170 --> 00:48:42,470
Oh—hmm?

719
00:48:42,710 --> 00:48:43,890
Are you okay?

720
00:48:45,850 --> 00:48:46,860
I’m fine.

721
00:48:49,090 --> 00:48:49,940
Lin.

722
00:48:54,080 --> 00:48:55,260
I think

723
00:48:56,310 --> 00:48:57,810
we should stop talking.

724
00:49:05,140 --> 00:49:06,480
That’s so cruel.

725
00:49:09,940 --> 00:49:11,360
I’m sorry.

726
00:49:12,780 --> 00:49:14,270
I kind of expected it already.

727
00:49:16,490 --> 00:49:18,860
Is that friend that important to you, Nao?

728
00:49:39,540 --> 00:49:40,500
Suer.

729
00:49:41,650 --> 00:49:42,840
Don’t go yet.

730
00:49:44,330 --> 00:49:45,560
Ouch.

731
00:49:46,220 --> 00:49:47,430
Hey, you.

732
00:49:49,760 --> 00:49:50,810
Are you okay?

733
00:49:51,240 --> 00:49:52,270
Get up first.

734
00:49:56,770 --> 00:49:57,720
Suer.

735
00:49:58,230 --> 00:49:59,660
Don’t go yet, okay?

736
00:50:01,800 --> 00:50:03,430
Stay and talk to me first.

737
00:50:08,630 --> 00:50:10,340
What happened to you?

738
00:50:13,050 --> 00:50:14,650
What did you do?

739
00:50:16,850 --> 00:50:18,860
Why are you covered in injuries?

740
00:50:22,490 --> 00:50:24,280
Why didn’t you contact me at all?

741
00:50:25,250 --> 00:50:26,340
I know.

742
00:50:26,580 --> 00:50:28,580
You told them not to tell me.

743
00:50:29,200 --> 00:50:31,320
Why are you being this cruel to me?

744
00:50:32,770 --> 00:50:34,140
Did I do something wrong?

745
00:50:49,270 --> 00:50:50,380
I’m sorry.

746
00:50:56,170 --> 00:50:57,770
Don’t be like this again.

747
00:50:58,860 --> 00:51:01,190
Don’t disappear without telling me again.

748
00:51:21,090 --> 00:51:22,260
Are you feeling better?

749
00:51:24,910 --> 00:51:25,860
Can you tell me?

750
00:51:26,320 --> 00:51:27,520
Where did you go?

751
00:51:29,790 --> 00:51:30,820
Work.

752
00:51:31,180 --> 00:51:33,520
Then why didn’t you contact me back at all?

753
00:51:37,950 --> 00:51:39,000
What are you doing?

754
00:51:44,880 --> 00:51:45,820
Packing.

755
00:51:46,930 --> 00:51:47,870
Where are you going?

756
00:51:48,870 --> 00:51:49,890
To see my brother.

757
00:51:50,780 --> 00:51:52,200
How long will you be gone?

758
00:51:53,070 --> 00:51:54,540
Will you come back?

759
00:51:56,900 --> 00:51:57,860
I don’t know.

760
00:51:58,380 --> 00:52:00,250
Are you still mad at me about Lin?

761
00:52:02,480 --> 00:52:03,790
I don’t get it.

762
00:52:05,180 --> 00:52:06,730
Why are you so angry?

763
00:52:08,160 --> 00:52:09,710
When I don’t like someone

764
00:52:10,650 --> 00:52:12,110
I just stop talking to them completely.

765
00:52:13,070 --> 00:52:14,870
But when it’s someone I really like

766
00:52:15,370 --> 00:52:17,230
why won’t you let me have that?

767
00:52:18,090 --> 00:52:19,310
Are you dating her now?

768
00:52:21,000 --> 00:52:22,460
I stopped talking to Lin.

769
00:52:23,800 --> 00:52:24,770
Because of me?

770
00:52:25,170 --> 00:52:25,950
No.

771
00:52:28,420 --> 00:52:29,930
Why are you still mad at me?

772
00:52:32,080 --> 00:52:33,630
I already stopped talking to Lin too.

773
00:52:37,530 --> 00:52:38,580
I’m not angry.

774
00:52:40,640 --> 00:52:41,630
I just

775
00:52:43,182 --> 00:52:44,044
maybe I’m just tired.

776
00:52:50,630 --> 00:52:51,700
Tired of what?

777
00:52:57,800 --> 00:52:59,890
I really don’t understand you, Suer.

778
00:53:00,660 --> 00:53:02,530
Why are you always like this?

779
00:53:03,350 --> 00:53:04,380
I know

780
00:53:04,750 --> 00:53:06,720
no matter who comes to me

781
00:53:07,180 --> 00:53:08,520
you hate them all.

782
00:53:09,080 --> 00:53:10,690
Because you’re attached to me.

783
00:53:11,200 --> 00:53:12,550
You’re angry that

784
00:53:12,750 --> 00:53:14,340
I don’t have time for you.

785
00:53:14,630 --> 00:53:16,020
Like in high school

786
00:53:16,530 --> 00:53:18,080
when you avoided me.

787
00:53:18,530 --> 00:53:20,750
After that I talked less to that girl.

788
00:53:21,500 --> 00:53:23,000
I always gave in to you.

789
00:53:23,630 --> 00:53:25,420
Just because you said you didn’t like it.

790
00:53:26,030 --> 00:53:27,640
But when I don’t give in

791
00:53:27,840 --> 00:53:29,610
why do we have to fight?

792
00:53:30,420 --> 00:53:32,450
Are you not even going to let me date anyone?

793
00:53:32,800 --> 00:53:34,410
Not even let me get married?

794
00:53:34,740 --> 00:53:37,120
That’s just a normal part of life, right?

795
00:53:38,010 --> 00:53:39,710
What is your problem?

796
00:53:40,300 --> 00:53:43,420
- We never fight about anything else
- What do you mean, “what is my problem?”

797
00:53:43,930 --> 00:53:46,580
- Just break up with me then
- Break up?

798
00:53:47,600 --> 00:53:49,420
We’ve been friends for six years.

799
00:53:49,690 --> 00:53:51,450
We’ve always been together.

800
00:53:52,020 --> 00:53:53,910
I really don’t understand you, Suer.

801
00:53:54,830 --> 00:53:56,740
You’re my closest friend.

802
00:53:57,040 --> 00:53:58,360
I used to think about it.

803
00:53:58,560 --> 00:54:00,200
I wanted you to be my best man.

804
00:54:00,480 --> 00:54:02,360
And our kids would be best friends.

805
00:54:02,660 --> 00:54:05,000
I want you in my life forever.

806
00:54:05,850 --> 00:54:07,170
That’s not going to happen.

807
00:54:08,280 --> 00:54:09,160
Nao.

808
00:54:09,860 --> 00:54:11,880
If that’s the future you imagined,

809
00:54:14,170 --> 00:54:15,680
I won’t be in your life anymore.

810
00:54:16,710 --> 00:54:19,750
We’ve been friends for six years, right?

811
00:54:22,210 --> 00:54:23,650
That’s not true, Nao.

812
00:54:26,850 --> 00:54:28,820
I was never just your friend.

813
00:54:32,300 --> 00:54:33,620
I like you.

814
00:54:35,790 --> 00:54:37,720
Even before I saw you as a friend.

815
00:54:39,600 --> 00:54:40,850
Since Grade 10.

816
00:54:41,720 --> 00:54:43,130
Until now, third year of college.

817
00:54:44,610 --> 00:54:50,510
Six years. It’s a long time to love someone alone like this.

818
00:54:51,810 --> 00:54:53,250
It hurts every time.

819
00:54:54,080 --> 00:54:55,520
When I see you talking to someone else.

820
00:54:55,870 --> 00:54:57,780
I’m jealous, but I have no right.

821
00:54:58,590 --> 00:55:00,020
In the end,

822
00:55:00,940 --> 00:55:02,470
you still see me as just a friend.

823
00:55:06,230 --> 00:55:07,410
I might be selfish.

824
00:55:07,810 --> 00:55:08,680
Yes.

825
00:55:10,700 --> 00:55:12,830
But if I have to keep watching you love someone else,

826
00:55:13,140 --> 00:55:14,340
I can’t do it.

827
00:55:17,940 --> 00:55:19,060
I’ve decided.

828
00:55:20,640 --> 00:55:22,850
If I have to watch you be with someone else,

829
00:55:24,790 --> 00:55:25,820
I’d rather disappear.

830
00:55:28,780 --> 00:55:29,860
Really?

831
00:55:30,590 --> 00:55:32,100
Are you serious?

832
00:55:35,590 --> 00:55:37,000
I already thought about it.

833
00:55:37,830 --> 00:55:39,100
When I told you,

834
00:55:39,960 --> 00:55:41,350
you probably wouldn’t believe me.

835
00:55:43,870 --> 00:55:45,560
But if I wait for you to realize it yourself,

836
00:55:46,840 --> 00:55:48,600
that day will never come.

837
00:55:50,540 --> 00:55:51,930
I’m sorry.

838
00:55:52,890 --> 00:55:55,220
For making you cry.

839
00:55:56,430 --> 00:55:57,840
For hurting you too.

840
00:55:59,660 --> 00:56:01,460
But if this didn’t happen,

841
00:56:02,480 --> 00:56:04,380
I’d never have the courage to confess.

842
00:56:07,510 --> 00:56:09,380
I would’ve kept it for six years otherwise.

843
00:56:12,250 --> 00:56:14,280
I always thought we were just friends.

844
00:56:14,830 --> 00:56:16,110
I…

845
00:56:16,910 --> 00:56:18,810
don’t fit into your world at all.

846
00:56:21,520 --> 00:56:24,560
- Why don’t you like someone else instead?
- I’ve loved you for six years.

847
00:56:26,290 --> 00:56:28,690
Don’t give me any opinions.

848
00:56:30,190 --> 00:56:31,640
If it’s not you,

849
00:56:32,810 --> 00:56:33,980
I won’t love anyone else.

850
00:56:38,290 --> 00:56:40,560
I guess I can’t be your friend anymore.

851
00:56:46,620 --> 00:56:48,180
What do you want me to do?

852
00:56:52,830 --> 00:56:54,400
Please open your heart to me.

853
00:56:55,900 --> 00:56:57,510
Not as your best friend,

854
00:56:58,420 --> 00:56:59,940
but...

855
00:57:02,480 --> 00:57:05,180
as a man who loves you, Nao.

856
00:57:16,440 --> 00:57:19,746
- So… are we dating now?
- No.

857
00:57:20,186 --> 00:57:22,280
It means I’m letting you try to date me.

858
00:57:22,480 --> 00:57:23,693
Why don’t you just be my boyfriend already?

859
00:57:23,817 --> 00:57:26,031
We’ll see how it goes first.

860
00:57:26,208 --> 00:57:29,462
Just go ask P’Jo how he did it when he was courting me.

861
00:57:29,604 --> 00:57:32,222
- What did he say?
- “Go big or go home.”

862
00:57:32,320 --> 00:57:33,435
I love you, Duennao.

863
00:57:33,760 --> 00:57:35,013
Damn.

864
00:57:35,173 --> 00:57:38,124
So what are you going to do about Suer?

865
00:57:38,706 --> 00:57:42,222
I really like being with you. I’ve realized I can’t live without you anymore.
